Start it in a separate terminal on the robot:

```bash
ssh rocket@192.168.8.221
export ROS_DOMAIN_ID=138
source /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash
source ~/gr4_ws/install/setup.bash

python3 ~/gr4_ws/tools/mission_run_logger.py
```

Then control it from another terminal with:

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'new_run'}"
```

Add a manual mark:

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark before_side_align'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark object_detection_correct'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark docking sucessfull'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark docking sucessfull_after_changeing_goal_x_from_137_to_134'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark docking unsucessfull'}"

ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'mark reseting_start_position'}"
```

Check logger status:

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'status'}"
ros2 topic echo /mission_run_logger_status
```

End the run manually:

```bash
ros2 topic pub --once /mission_run_logger_command std_msgs/msg/String "{data: 'end_run'}"
```

Logs are saved here:

```bash
~/gr4_ws/mission_run_logs
```

It should also auto-start when you send `trolley_ready`, but I’d start it manually with `new_run` when testing so the timing is clean.
